title:
As Ukraine Scores Gains, 
U.S. Looks to Peace Talks
description: American arms are flowing, but officials in Washington question how much territory Ukraine or Russia can win with winter approaching.

title: Iran Issues First Known Death Sentence for Protester
description: Authorities say they have issued indictments of more than 1,000 people in Tehran alone, and on Sunday a judge in the southern province of Hormozgan said that 164 more protesters would be charged with a range of offenses.

title: China Dials Back Property Restrictions in Bid to Reverse Economic Slide
description: Partial easing of housing-sector rules comes as Beijing also seeks to lessen economic toll of strict Covid controls.

title: Dozens of Americans Are Barred From Leaving China, Adding to Tensions
description: Californian Henry Cai, who got into a business dispute, has been targeted by exit bans for nearly five years.

title: Deadly Explosion Hits Busy Istanbul Pedestrian Street
description: The bomb blast killed at least six people and wounded 53 others, Turkey’s president said.

title: Some Russia Sanctions Could Extend Beyond War's End, Yellen Says
description: The U.S. Treasury secretary says any eventual peace agreement between Russia and Ukraine would involve a review of the penalties the U.S. and its allies have imposed on Moscow’s economy.

title: President Biden, Xi Jinping to Spell Out Priorities and Red Lines During Bali Meeting
description: The leaders are set to meet face-to-face Monday for the first time since Mr. Biden became president, though they had extensive interactions when they served as vice presidents of their respective countries.

title: Ukraine Races to Restore Power, Water in Kherson After Russian Withdrawal
description: Ukrainian forces that swept into the southern city over the weekend were greeted by jubilant crowds, but a municipal official said the humanitarian situation in the city was critical.

title: China's Global Port Investments Give Rise to Security Worries
description: The expanding network could make it easier for Beijing to service a Chinese navy that has become one of Washington’s biggest military concerns, analysts say.

title: Israeli President Hands Mandate to Benjamin Netanyahu to Form Government
description: Mr. Netanyahu has promised to form a purely right-wing coalition including ultranationalist and religious parties.

title: Departure of Tech Workers Weighs on Russian Economy
description: President Vladimir Putin’s troop mobilization for the Ukraine war has caused sales to drop and well-paid employees to flee abroad.

title: G-20 Discord Likely to Thwart Efforts to Boost Sagging Global Economy
description: War in Ukraine, inflation and U.S.-China tensions are all dividing major economies and making any coordinated response difficult.

title: Inside the Kyiv Power Cuts: Cold Food, Scheduled Vacuuming, Struggling Businesses
description: Russia has targeted Ukraine’s electricity grid in an attempt to break civilians’ will, resulting in rolling power cuts in Kyiv. Residents are adapting.
